 # Active Directory Home Lab

## Overview
Built a Windows Active Directory lab to simulate a real-world enterprise environment and perform common IT support and system administration tasks.

## Objectives
- Manage user accounts and permissions
- Configure Group Policy Objects (GPOs)
- Simulate onboarding and offboarding processes
- Troubleshoot authentication and access issues

## Tools & Technologies
- Windows Server
- Active Directory
- Virtual Machines (VirtualBox/VMware)
- Windows 10/11

## Steps Performed
1. Installed and configured Windows Server as a Domain Controller
2. Created users, groups, and organizational units (OUs)
3. Applied Group Policy settings to control user environments
4. Simulated user login scenarios and permission restrictions
5. Performed password resets and tested account lockouts

## Key Takeaways
- Developed hands-on experience with Active Directory user and access management
- Strengthened troubleshooting skills for login and permission-related issues
- Gained practical understanding of enterprise IT environments

## Future Improvements
- Automate user creation using PowerShell scripts
- Simulate security events such as failed login attempts and account lockouts
